{
  "texts": [
    "This yields a total of 25 unknowns.",
    "Meanwhile, the θ vectors provide 5 × 5 × 2 = 50 constraints.",
    "The latter suffice to solve for all β vectors, except for an overall scale, which is degenerate.",
    "The reference position β 0 of the source is not solved for, either, as it also degenerate.",
    "Another example, this time for a galaxy lens, appears in the study of B0128+437 by Wagner and Williams (2020), using four images with three components each."
  ]
}